Winter hair tips that have helped keep my hair healthy during these dry, colder months: 
*Use a wide tooth comb like this one from @t3micro to detangle hair and brush through knots to prevent hair fall out. It also helps add volume to flat ends over a teasing comb that can break fine hair 
*Lower the heat on your curling iron to prevent curls from falling limp! I love the @t3micro single pass because the ceramic barrel also adds shine and eliminates frizz
*Apply dry shampoo at night & refresh with a little styling in the AM to prevent having to wash your hair frequently. The Airebrush Duo gives a blow out look without the hassle and IonFlow technology delivers 60% more consistent heat for frizz-free hair with less damage 

Use code AMIT320 sitewide @t3micro on my favorite tools above #t3micro #t3partner #winterhairhacks #winterhairtips

Finally trying out the viral @hauslabs Skintech medium coverage foundation & here are my thoughts… 
-I get the hype..this finish is stunning. It’s similar to the cult fave Armani Luminous Silk, but it doesn’t oxidize like the Armani can on some skin types 
-it’s formulated with fermented Arnica which helps combat redness & inflammation 
-it has 51 shades but the shade system works a little differently (like what we know to be warm shades are their cool shades, etc etc..little hard to get used to at first) 

I definitely think worth a try, ideally in store so you can shade match easily. I’m testing 240 Light Medium Warm & 270 Light Medium Neutral

When I say my hair has never been this healthy or strong in years…🥹🙌🏽Hair & scalp health has been trending, but it’s been around for centuries, and I’m going to show you the things I’ve been doing that have been making a big difference. Using all @fableandmane today including their newest launch:
 
-Dry combing with this wooden neem scalp massager to detangle prevents less hair fall out. It also and helps promote blood circulation to the scalp..I never used to do this & do it daily now!
 
-Pre-wash hair oiling truly works! It’s not immediate but you will see stronger strands overtime. And having babies for almost a decade left me with cycles of thin, brittle hair so I have witnessed the change first hand. I’ll use about 3-4 droppers of the HoliRoots Oil in sections focused on the scalp and then put some all the way to the ends leaving on overnight or at least for 1 hour
 
-adding an after-wash hair oil to wet and dry hair has given me the shine and luster that my dry hair lacks. This MahaMane Smooth + Shine Oil is very lightweight and helps keep my hair looking 💯 in between wash days 
 
Let me know what you’ve been doing or switched up recently that you’ve noticed has helped with your hair too! @Sephora #fableandmanepartner #fableandmane #hairhealth #hairgrowth

Summer swimwear I have found to be both cute & functional for the ever changing mom bod 🫶🏽 Couple reminders if you’re a new mom or just find yourself in a transitional phase with your body. I spent so many years just worried about how I’d be perceived in my bathing suit, especially after kids, because who has the time to suck it in or stand up straight when you have tiny people hanging all over you?? 🤪 What I’ve realized is 1) no one really cares, they’re too busy worried about their own situations & 2) the people that matter the most (your kids) won’t remember the stretch marks or the extra pounds, but they will remember if mom got in the water & had fun with them. So with these warmer months approaching and possibly some pool days ahead don’t let that self doubt or those insecurities get to you! Wear that suit, jump in that pool and make those memories!! 

Look 1: love my @ta3swim one piece..these have seen me through many phases of in between babies & postpartum life. They suck in all the right places 🙌🏽 Sarong is @loversfriendsla & no longer avail but linking a few similar & budget friendly options 

Look 2: I have this @aguabenditasw suit in black too and it’s so cute if you don’t want to show your arms or need more coverage in that area. The sheer cover up is older from @forever21 but linking similar 

Look 3: I live in coverups that are cute because I’m always in and out of the water grabbing something. This one can easily be worn as a dress to and is so comfy from @sundaysthelabel

Dear Mom, through the lens of lifestyle expert and mother of three, Ami Desai. 

As a first-generation immigrant born in the U.S., Ami Desai knows the importance of representation. Her mother taught her the value of self-confidence by leading through example, balancing a successful career with her role as a present parent. Ami saw the need for more South Asian representation in the media world, and with her mother’s guidance, she has become a successful entrepreneur, building her own brand and community as a lifestyle expert. Now, as a mother herself, Ami aspires to pass on those same values to her own family. 

#dearmom #venusetfleur #mothersday

Date night expectation vs reality 🥰 we may have called it a night before 10pm, but we tried & we made US a priority 🫶🏽 It’s not always easy but so necessary. Two of my biggest takeaways I’ve learned over the years on how to show up for each other & really prioritize our relationship (would love to hear any tips you have too):

-Take even the littles pockets of time that open up & seize them. Last year we made a last minute decision to attend this festival to see the Lumineers and now it’s sort of become our little date night tradition 

-Motivate each other. I’ve realized my partner is not only my biggest cheerleader but also has become my biggest motivator in life to accomplish all the goals I have. Checking in on each other and seeing what we need to really make those desires reality can take you so far

And there’s no shame in my game 😝 Especially because I can feel good about pampering myself with all my fave @patchology masks that now come in resealable 2 packs, which means less waste 🙌🏽 Thanks to their efforts with the Rare Cycle initiative, being sustainable has never been easier.
